    "body": "If you haven’t already, check out our [contributing guidelines](https://github.com/Expensify/ReactNativeChat/blob/main/contributingGuides/CONTRIBUTING.md) for onboarding and email contributors@expensify.com to request to join our Slack channel!\n___\n\n**Version Number:** V9.3.58-0\n**Reproducible in staging?:** Yes\n**Reproducible in production?:** Yes\n**If this was caught during regression testing, add the test name, ID and link from BrowserStack:** https://test-management.browserstack.com/projects/2219752/test-runs/TR-17825/folder/13176706/68951928/1320797614\n**Email or phone of affected tester (no customers):** dreamnitethedragon+vegst@gmail.com\n**Issue reported by:** Applause Internal Team\n**Bug source:** Regression TC Execution\n**Device used:** Redmi note 10s android 13\n**App Component:** Money Requests\n\n## Action Performed:\n1. Launch app\n2. Go to company cards\n3. Add a region Bank direct feed and assign to self to import card transactions\n ( card name - Ht )\n4. Search for \"ai\" / \"io\"\n5. Search for \"gh\" / \"uy\"\n\n## Expected Result:\nFor any input with zero results:\nTable header should be hidden\nEmpty state (e.g., “No results found”) should be displayed consistently\n\n## Actual Result:\n*For \"ai\" and \"io\":\n\nNo results are displayed\nTable header is NOT hidden\n“No results found” message is NOT shown\n\n\n*For \"gh\" and \"uy\":\n\nNo results are displayed\nTable header is hidden\n“No results found” message is shown\n\nStep 12 in regression step failed\n\n## Workaround:\nUnknown\n\n## Platforms:\n- [x] Android: App\n- [ ] Android: mWeb Chrome\n- [ ] iOS: App\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Safari\n- [ ] iOS: mWeb Chrome\n- [x] Windows: Chrome\n- [ ] MacOS: Chrome / Safari\n\n## Screenshots/Videos\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/118d2420-ede9-4615-af15-4bd5bf7fd1af\n\n[View all open jobs on GitHub](https://github.com/Expensify/App/issues?q=is%3Aopen+is%3Aissue+label%3A%22Help+Wanted%22)\n\n<details><summary>Issue Owner<